column11: 1.  The Education, Skills and Training domain score is calculated by ranking the indicators, transforming them to a standard normal distribution and combining them using weights generated by factor analysis.  The score is then ranked to provide the education domain rank.
2. The working age people without qualifications indicator uses exactly the same data as the SIMD 2009.
3. The 17-21 year olds enrolling into higher education is the same indicator as in SIMD 2009. Values of less than 5% have been suppressed with an asterisk (*).
4.  The School pupil absences indicator is an estimate of pupil attendance and is the proportion of half days at school when pupils were absent from school.

5. The school absence and SQA performance data has been treated for disclosure by swapping the data zones for a small percentage of records before producing the aggregate results.  This has a negligible effect on the overall trends, but ensures that the confidentiality of individual records are maintained.
6. Metadata for each indicator included in the education domain can be found in the SIMD technical notes.
